**Oatmeal Raisin Cookies are a classic and wholesome treat that can be enjoyed any time of the day. To make these delicious cookies, start by mixing together rolled oats, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt in a bowl. In a separate bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy, then beat in an egg and vanilla extract. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients until a dough forms, then fold in raisins. Drop spoonfuls of the dough onto a lined baking sheet and bake in a preheated oven until golden brown and slightly crispy around the edges. The result is a batch of chewy and satisfying cookies that are perfect for snacking or sharing with friends and family. **Black Bean Brownies are a delicious and healthy dessert option that is gluten-free and packed with protein and fiber. To make this brownie, start by blending cooked black beans, eggs, cocoa powder, honey, vanilla extract, and baking powder in a food processor until smooth. Then, fold in dark chocolate chips and chopped walnuts. Pour the mixture into a greased baking dish and bake in the oven until the brownies are set and slightly firm to the touch. The result is a fudgy and decadent dessert that is rich in flavor and nutrients. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream for a delicious and satisfying treat.
